On Fri, 17 Aug 2001 wilden1(-at-)juno.com wrote:

> Take a pair of channel lock pliers and brace them against the engine
> block and pull your tubes out.

to clearify that a little, the push rods come out through the
heads. unlike the older engines in which they were squeezed between the
head and block.

so        |           |
    block |___________|  head
               cyl      
           ___________
          |           |
           ===========   <-pushrod tube
          |           |

      it comes out---> this way--->

